Problem statement: Library Login form
1. For the above problem capture the requirements of the client and document them, also review it with acceptance criteria.
• Open the website “github.com”.
• Login to your github using your gmail.id.
• Click on create new repository.
• Click on create a new file.
• Enter the file name.
• Upload the file of Structure of srs.
• Click on commit on new file.
• Click on your file.
• Copy the permalink.
• Go to your jira account.
• Click on the issue created.
• Go to the description, click on the link symbol, paste the link which you have copied
• Enter the test to display as “Structure of srs”.
• Click on Save.
2. Identify and document two associate risk for the above case study .
• Login to your jira account
• Click on apps
• Download the risk register app
• Go to risk model
• Edit the impact, probability and level of risks
• Click on save changes
• Go to the project modify the risk assessment
• Click on save
• Go to risks
• Click on create a risk register
• Enter the risk project name
• Click on create
• Click on risk matrix
• The risk matrix will be displayed
3. Create user stories and draw UML diagram for the above requirement.
• Go to jira software
• Click on get it for free.
Sign in with your google account
Enter Site name
• Your site starts to build.
• Add project details. Like enter your team name or project name.
• Click on create project.
• Enter your teammates gmail id
• Click on done the window appears as below.
• Click on create.
• Enter the issue type as story.
• Enter summary as Library login.
• Enter the description as
AS A student
I WANT TO login for library
THEN I should get the list of the books available.
• Click on create.
• The user story will be created.
UML diagram
• Go to lucid chart in google
• Login to your google account.
• Click on New > lucid chart> blank diagram.
• Draw the uml diagram as below.
• Go to your jira account.
• Click on the issue created.
• Go to the description, click on the link symbol.
• Paste the link which you have copied, Enter test to display as UML diagram.
4. Write the test suite for the above requirement.
• Login to your jira account.
• Click on projects > create project
• Select Bug tracking.
• Click on use template.
• Add Name of the project.
• Select all in type, status, and assignee as current user.
• Go to Apps, Download the Requirements & Test management for Jira.
• Select your project.
• Click on Enable.
• Click on next
• Select Epic in Requirement.
• Select Bug in Test case.
• Select Improvement in Test plan.
• Select Task in Test Execution.
• Click on Next.
• Select New feature in Issue type.
• Click on next.
• Click on add automatically.
• Click on next.
• Click on start Adventure.
• Click on Create Requirement
• Enter the Epic name and description.
• Click on Create.
• Your Requirement will be created.
• Go to Test cases.
• Click on Create Test Case.
• Enter Summary.
• Click on create.
• Your test case will be created.
• Create 4 Test cases as below.
• Select all the Test cases.
• Click on Create Execution.
• Enter the summary.
• Click on create.
• Go to Test Execution.
• Click on the Issue key.
• Select each test case and edit the results.
• Click on save.
• Do for all the test cases as below.
• Click on Reports > Test execution.
• Select all in Test Requirement folder.
• Click on generate.
• The Bar graph will be created as below.
